			<section id="two" class="wrapper style2 align-center">
				<div class="container">
					<header>
						<a name="implementation"></a>
						<h2>Implementation</h2>
						<p>To start implementation with the UAPI, simply start by adding the following to your POM.xml (you can also add the jar file to your build path if you don't use maven, in which case skip the pom.xml)</p>
            <a name="setuppom"></a>
						<h2>Setup pom.xml (maven)</h2>
            <p>Add the following repository and dependency.</p>
						<pre class="language-markup"><code style="text-align: left;">
            &lt;repositories&gt;
              &lt;repository&gt;
                &lt;id&gt;ulticraft-repo&lt;/id&gt;
                &lt;url&gt;https://bitbucket.org/overcode/ulticraft-repo/raw/&lt;/url&gt;
              &lt;/repository&gt;
            &lt;/repositories&gt;
            &lt;dependencies&gt;
              &lt;dependency&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;com.ulticraft.uapi&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;UAPI&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;version&gt;1.0.22&lt;/version&gt;
              &lt;/dependency&gt;
            &lt;/dependencies&gt;
            </code></pre>
						<a name="setupclass"></a>
						<h2>Extend main plugin class</h2>
						<p>When implementing in bukkit/spigot, you typically extend JavaPlugin, with the UAPI, extend with UltimatePlugin</p>
            <pre class="language-java"><code style="text-align: left;">
              import com.ulticraft.uapi.plugin.UltimatePlugin;

              public class HelloUAPI extends UltimatePlugin
              {
                  @Override
                  public void onEnable()
                  {
                      super.onEnable(); //Ensure this is the first call
                  
                      //Your enable code here
                  }
                
                  @Override
                  public void onDisable()
                  {
                      //Your disable code here
                      
                      super.onDisable(); //Ensure this is the last call
                  }
              }
            </code></pre>
					</header>
					<header>
            <a name="components"></a>
            <h2>Components</h2>
            <p>Components are what make the UAPI the UAPI! Including the dispatcher of many other things</p>
			<a name="dispatcher"></a>
			<h2>The Dispatcher</h2>
			<p>Since you are now extending the UltimatePlugin, You can call from the dispatcher easily, simply by using the given methods.</p>
            <pre class="language-java"><code style="text-align: left;">
              import com.ulticraft.uapi.plugin.UltimatePlugin;

              public class HelloUAPI extends UltimatePlugin
              {
                  @Override
                  public void onEnable()
                  {
                      super.onEnable(); //Ensure this is the first call
                      
                      //First level output (colored)
                      i("This is general info");
                      s("Success! This is green!");
                      w("Warning: This is yellow!");
                      f("FATAL: This is RED!");
                      v("Verbose: Verbose information");
                      o("OVERBose: More Verbose information");
                      
                      //Sub level output (dark colored)
                      si("This is sub-general info, dark gray");
                      ss("Sub-Success! This is dark green!");
                      sw("Partial-Warning: This is gold!");
                      sf("Sub FATAL: This is dark RED!");
                      sv("Sub Verbose: Verbose sub-information");
                      so("Sub OVERBose: More Verbose sub-information");
                  }
                
                  @Override
                  public void onDisable()
                  {
                      //Your disable code here
                      
                      super.onDisable(); //Ensure this is the last call
                  }
              }
            </code></pre>
            
            <p>Outputting the following</p>
            <img src="images/dev/dispatcher.png"></img>
			<a name="listeners"></a>
			<h2>Listeners & Registry</h2>
			<p>As an UltimatePlugin, you can now simply register anything that has access to your main class (UltimatePlugin) very simply, pl.register(this).</p>
			<pre class="language-java"><code style="text-align: left;">
              public class TestEvents implements Listener
              {
			      //Ensure to instantiate this in your HelloUAPI onEnable method
			      public TestEvents(HelloUAPI pl)
				  {
				      pl.register(this)  //Boom! all the events below are now registered
				  }
				  
				  @EventHandler
				  public void onPlayerJoin(PlayerJoinEvent event)
				  {
				      //Fired event.
				  }
			  }
            </code></pre>
			<a name="usound"></a>
			<h2>USound (Custom Sounds)</h2>
			<p>With UAPI, you now have the ability to create Sound objects based on sounds from resource packs! Given, players have the resource pack, they will hear all the sounds without having to override minecraft sounds.<p>
			<pre class="language-java"><code style="text-align: left;">
              public class TestSounds implements Listener
              {
			      //Ensure to instantiate this in your HelloUAPI onEnable method
			      public TestSounds(HelloUAPI pl)
				  {
				      pl.register(this)  //Register the event below
				  }
				  
				  @EventHandler
				  public void onPlayerJoin(PlayerJoinEvent event)
				  {
				      USound sound = new USound("custom.sound.from.resource.pack");
					  sound.play(e.getPlayer());  //Simply play it standard volume and pitch
					  sound.play(e.getPlayer(), 1f, 2f);  //Play the sound at twice the pitch
				  }
			  }
            </code></pre>
					</header>
